[Jinxed Idol](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Jinxed Idol) isn't the best choice, since it gives your opponent a way to get rid of any creatures you might want to give to them (like, say, [Steel Golem](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Steel Golem)). Or even just that [Gilded Drake](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gilded Drake) you used to steal their general-- It's probably doing you more good than them.  

Another point, though: Obviously this is great for the cursed things you'd use with [Donate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Donate) or whatever, but let's not also forget that there are a lot of cards out there that don't really care who their controller is, including EDH staples like [Arrest](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arrest) or [Pithing Needle](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pithing Needle). Once you've cast these things, you might as well donate them the next time you have the mana to spare, to increase your lifegain and card advantage.  

@Cyberium: This wouldn't work too well with the vows, though, since the "you" in "can't attack you" is the aura's controller.

@0pp0  

That rule was changed with M10 or something I think it was, the current ruling is this.  

110.5a A token is both owned and controlled by the player under whose control it entered the battlefield.
